BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
To find the slope of a line from its graph, we first need to identify two points that the line passes through. It is wise to choose points with integer coordinates. For this problem, we choose [`[$pt1]`] and [`[$pt2]\text{.}`]

Next, we sketch a slope triangle and find the _rise_ and _run_. In the sketch below, the rise is [`3`] and the run is [`8\text{.}`]

>> [@image(insertGraph($image_2), width=>282)@]*  <<

[```\text{slope}=\frac{\text{rise}}{\text{run}}=\frac{3}{8}```]

This line's slope is [`[$m]\text{.}`]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

